sed all the trophy winners as club world champions with the same title to the [[FIFA Club World Cup]] winners, then as official<ref name=\":F152322\">\"Official (''plural'' officials), from the Latin '' offici\u0101lis.'' 1. The official word is also used to refer to what is recognized or derives from an authority. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.dictionary.com/browse/official|title=Official, definition|author=dictionary.com}} 2. Approved by the government or someone in power. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english-spanish/official|title=official|author=dictionary.cambridge.org}} It is synonymous with legal, legitimate, approved. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.thesaurus.com/browse/official|title=Synonyms for official|author=thesaurus.com}}</ref><ref name=\":F154232\">For FIFA statute, official competitions are those for representative teams organized by FIFA or any confederation. Representative teams are usually national teams but also club teams that represent a confederation in the interconfederal competitions or a member association in a continental competition cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/the-fifa-statutes-in-force-as-of-27-april-2016-2782908.pdf?cloudid=vga5sv1yxeayptzrdudx|title=FIFA Statutes, April 2016 edition|page=5|format=PDF}} cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/statistical-kit-fifa-club-world-cup-uae-2018.pdf?cloudid=mkbo3nwk4btahl9gwtwl|title=FIFA Club World Cup UAE 2018: Statistical-kit|date=10 December 2018|page=13|format=PDF}} cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/Regulations/uefaorg/Regulations/02/55/82/79/2558279_DOWNLOAD.pdf|title=2018/19 UEFA Champions League regulations|page=10}}</ref> \"[[Intercontinental Cup (football)#International participation|world champions]]\" FIFA.<ref name=\":F154233222\">\u201cWhile it does not promote the statistical unification of tournaments, that is, has not absorbed to the Intercontinental Cup (merged with FIFA Club World Cup in 2005), FIFA is the only organization with worldwide jurisdiction over continental confederations and, then, the only one that can confer a title on that level, ergo the title assigned by FIFA with Official Document to the winners of the Intercontinental Cup is legally a FIFA world title.\"  cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/the-fifa-statutes-in-force-as-of-27-april-2016-2782908.pdf?cloudid=vga5sv1yxeayptzrdudx|title=FIFA Statutes, April 2016 edition|last=|first=|date=|website=|page=19|format=PDF|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}} cfr.</ref><ref name=\"FIFA201732\">{{cite press release|date=27 October 2017|title=FIFA Council approves key organisational elements of the FIFA World Cup|url=https://www.fifa.com/about-fifa/news/y=2017/m=10/news=fifa-council-approves-key-organisational-elements-of-the-fifa-world-cu-2917722.html|publisher=FIFA|accessdate=27 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/fifa-acepta-propuesta-de-conembol-de-reconocer-titulos-de-copa-intercontinental-como-mundiales-de|title=FIFA acepta propuesta de CONMEBOL de reconocer t\u00edtulos de copa intercontinental como mundiales de clubes|date=29 October 2017|publisher=conmebol.com|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=\"kit201822\">{{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/statistical-kit-fifa-club-world-cup-uae-2018.pdf?cloudid=mkbo3nwk4btahl9gwtwl|title=FIFA Club World Cup UAE 2018: Statistical-kit|date=10 December 2018|page=13|format=PDF}}</ref>\n{{-}}\n\n==Match details==\n{{footballbox\n|date=9 December 1990\n|time=12:00\n|team1=[[A.C. Milan|Milan]] {{flagicon|ITA}}\n|score=3\u20130\n|report=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/3308/\n|team2={{flagicon|PAR|1990}} [[Club Olimpia|Olimpia]]\n|goals1=[[Frank Rijkaard|Rijkaard]] {{goal|43||65}} <br/> [[Giovanni Stroppa|Stroppa]] {{goal|62}}\n|goals2=\n|stadium=[[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]], [[Tokyo]]\n|attendance=6